<subSubSection pageId="95" pageNumber="96" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="95.[264,1322,359,547]" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">
Diagnosis: Head always with a pair of cruciate postocellar bristles. Dorsocentral bristles in 2 or 3 pairs. Wing uniformly, lightly pigmented (with clear bands in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cui and Marshall" authorityYear="2005" box="[1070,1235,399,425]" class="Insecta" family="Sphaeroceridae" genus="Robustagramma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="95" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cultriforme">
<emphasis box="[1070,1088,399,424]" italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1102,1235,399,424]" italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">cultriforme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis box="[1235,1243,399,424]" italics="true" pageId="95" pageNumber="96">)</emphasis>
; distal quarter of R conspicuously curved forward. Mid tibia with an additional small anterodorsal preapical bristle anterior to dorsal bristle. Sternite 5 of male with two patches of small black scales on posteromedial margin.
</paragraph>
